# PROJECT CONSTITUTION: gemini.mmd
## Almadeinah Medical Platform — Architectural Rules & Principles

> This file is the single source of truth for all architectural decisions.
> Every contributor (human or AI agent) MUST follow these rules without exception.
> Any deviation requires a formal update to this file first.

---

## RULE 1 — Strict Separation of Concerns

The codebase is divided into five distinct layers. Each layer has a single responsibility and may only communicate with the layers described below it.

```mermaid
graph TD
    A["📄 Pages / Dashboards<br/>(src/pages/)"] --> B["🪝 Custom Hooks<br/>(src/hooks/)"]
    B --> C["🌐 API Layer<br/>(src/api/)"]
    C --> D["🔌 Supabase Client<br/>(src/lib/supabaseClient.js)"]
    A --> E["🧩 UI Components<br/>(src/components/)"]
    B --> F["🗃️ Global Store<br/>(src/store/)"]
    E --> F
```

### Layer Mandates

| Layer | Can Import From | CANNOT Import From |
|---|---|---|
| `pages/` | `hooks/`, `components/`, `store/`, `utils/` | `api/` directly, `lib/` directly |
| `hooks/` | `api/`, `store/`, `utils/`, `lib/` | `components/`, `pages/` |
| `api/` | `lib/`, `utils/` | `hooks/`, `store/`, `components/`, `pages/` |
| `components/` | `store/`, `utils/` | `api/`, `hooks/` (use props/callbacks instead) |
| `store/` | `utils/` | Everything else |

> **Enforcement**: ESLint import-boundary rules will be configured to flag violations automatically.

---

## RULE 2 — Supabase Client is a Singleton

- There is exactly ONE Supabase client instance: `src/lib/supabaseClient.js`.
- Direct imports of `supabaseClient` are **only allowed** in `src/api/` and `src/lib/`.
- Pages, hooks, and components **must NEVER** call `supabase.from()` directly.
- All Supabase interactions are mediated through `src/api/` functions.

```
✅ CORRECT:  import { createAppointment } from '../api/appointments';
❌ FORBIDDEN: import { supabase } from '../lib/supabaseClient';  // in a page/component
```

---

## RULE 3 — Supabase Role-Based Access Control (RBAC)

### User Roles
The platform supports exactly two application roles stored in the `profiles` table:

| Role | Access Level | Dashboard Route |
|---|---|---|
| `patient` | Own data only (appointments, profile, payments) | `/dashboard/patient/*` |
| `admin` | All data + management operations | `/dashboard/admin/*` |

### Frontend Enforcement
- A `ProtectedRoute` component wraps all dashboard routes.
- It checks `useAuthStore` for the authenticated user's role.
- Unauthorized access redirects to `/unauthorized`, not a silent failure.

### Backend Enforcement (Supabase RLS)
Row Level Security MUST be enabled on every table containing user data. Anonymous/unauthenticated access is allowed only on publicly advertised tables (`doctors`, `clinics`, `services`).

> [!CAUTION]
> **Supabase RLS Role Syntax — MANDATORY**
>
> Always specify `TO anon, authenticated` (or `TO authenticated`) explicitly in every policy.
> Omitting the role defaults to the PostgreSQL `public` role, which is **NOT** the same as
> Supabase's `anon` or `authenticated` roles. This silently returns empty data to the browser.
>
> ```sql
> -- ❌ WRONG — defaults to {public} role, data will be empty in browser
> CREATE POLICY "..." ON doctors FOR SELECT USING (true);
>
> -- ✅ CORRECT — explicitly targets Supabase application roles
> CREATE POLICY "..." ON doctors FOR SELECT TO anon, authenticated USING (true);
> ```



**RLS Policy Matrix (as deployed — 2026-03-08):**

| Table | Anonymous | Patient (own) | Admin (all) |
|---|---|---|---|
| `doctors` | ✅ READ | ✅ READ | ✅ FULL |
| `clinics` | ✅ READ | ✅ READ | ✅ FULL |
| `clinic_services` | ✅ READ | ✅ READ | ✅ FULL |
| `scans` | ✅ READ | ✅ READ | ✅ FULL |
| `examinations` | ✅ READ | ✅ READ | ✅ FULL |
| `equipments` | ✅ READ | ✅ READ | ✅ FULL |
| `blogs` | ✅ READ | ✅ READ | ✅ FULL |
| `lab_tests_list` | ✅ READ | ✅ READ | ✔️ READ |
| `medical_packages` | ✅ READ | ✅ READ | ✅ FULL |
| `medical_tests_guide` | ✅ READ | ✅ READ | ✅ FULL |
| `appointments` | ❌ BLOCKED | ✅ OWN rows only | ✅ FULL |
| `profiles` | ❌ BLOCKED | ✅ OWN row only | ✅ FULL |
| `gastrointestinal...`| ✅ READ | ✅ READ | ✔️ READ |

> **Rule**: Any new table added to the schema MUST have RLS enabled and policies defined before being used in production.

