## RULE 4 — Payment API Security (CRITICAL)

```
🔴 ABSOLUTE RULE: Payment gateway secret keys MUST NEVER appear
   in any frontend file or any VITE_* environment variable.
   Doing so exposes the secret in the browser's JavaScript bundle.
```

### Approved Payment Architecture

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant Browser as 🌐 Browser (React)
    participant EdgeFn as ⚡ Supabase Edge Function
    participant Gateway as 💳 Payment Gateway API

    Browser->>EdgeFn: supabase.functions.invoke('process-payment', payload)
    Note over EdgeFn: Secret API key lives HERE (Supabase secret env)
    EdgeFn->>Gateway: POST /charges (with secret key)
    Gateway-->>EdgeFn: { status, transactionId }
    EdgeFn-->>Browser: { success: true, transactionId }
```

- **Frontend** (`src/api/payments/index.js`): Only calls `supabase.functions.invoke()` with public, non-sensitive data (amount, currency, booking ID).
- **Edge Function** (`supabase/functions/process-payment/index.ts`): Holds the secret key via `Deno.env.get('PAYMENT_SECRET_KEY')`.
- **Secret Storage**: Keys are set via `supabase secrets set PAYMENT_SECRET_KEY=...` CLI, never in `.env` files tracked by git.

---

## RULE 5 — Mobile-Readiness by Design

This frontend will eventually have a React Native companion app. All business logic must be portable:

- **Hooks are the API contract** between UI and data. The React Native app will re-use hooks logic.
- Components must accept data via **props only** (no fetching inside leaf components).
- Avoid web-specific APIs (`window`, `document`, `localStorage`) inside hooks. Use abstractions.

---

## RULE 6 — Internationalization (i18n)

- All user-facing strings must be externalised (no hardcoded Arabic/English).
- RTL layout is default; LTR must be an opt-in toggle.
- Date/time formatting must use Arabic locale helpers from `src/utils/dateFormatter.js`.

---

## RULE 7 — No Secret Data in Version Control

The `.gitignore` must always include:
- `.env` (Supabase URL + anon key)
- `.env.local`, `.env.production`
- Any file matching `*.secret.*`

The `VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY` is a **publishable** key and is safe to expose. All other keys are **secret** and must never be prefixed with `VITE_`.

---

## RULE 8 — Advanced Security & Penetration Prevention

> This rule formalises Phase 7 of the task plan. All four requirements below are **non-negotiable** before any production deployment.

### 8a — Input Validation & XSS Prevention

```
🔴 ZERO TOLERANCE: No user-supplied string may be inserted into the DOM
   or sent to the database without passing validation and sanitization first.
```

- **Validation**: All form input must pass a function from `src/utils/validators.js` before the API call is made. Hook-level guards are the minimum; server-side (Supabase check constraints) are preferred for critical fields.
- **Sanitization**: Free-text fields (names, addresses, notes) must be stripped of HTML before submission using `src/utils/sanitizer.js` (DOMPurify wrapper).
- **`dangerouslySetInnerHTML` ban**: This React prop is FORBIDDEN unless the content has passed through `DOMPurify.sanitize()` and the usage is explicitly documented.
- **URL/Route param validation**: Every `useParams()` value used in a Supabase query MUST be validated as a non-negative integer (or appropriate type) before use.

### 8b — Rate Limiting Rules

| Endpoint / Function | Limit | Window |
|---|---|---|
| `process-payment` Edge Function | 5 requests | per IP per 10 minutes |
| Auth sign-in / OTP Edge Functions | 10 attempts | per IP per hour |
| Public API (Supabase PostgREST) | Default Supabase limits apply | — |

- Implementation: **Upstash Redis** (`@upstash/ratelimit`) or Deno KV inside Edge Functions.
- On limit breach: return HTTP `429 Too Many Requests` with `Retry-After` header.

### 8c — Required Security Headers

All production responses must include:

| Header | Value |
|---|---|
| `Content-Security-Policy` | `default-src 'self'; script-src 'self'; style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline' fonts.googleapis.com; font-src fonts.gstatic.com; img-src 'self' data: *.supabase.co; connect-src 'self' *.supabase.co` |
| `X-Content-Type-Options` | `nosniff` |
| `X-Frame-Options` | `DENY` |
| `Referrer-Policy` | `strict-origin-when-cross-origin` |
| `Permissions-Policy` | `camera=(), microphone=(), geolocation=()` |
| `Strict-Transport-Security` | `max-age=31536000; includeSubDomains` |

### 8d — Pre-Deployment Security Audit (mandatory gate)

No code may be merged to `main` / deployed to production until **all** of the following pass:

```
[ ] npm audit — zero HIGH or CRITICAL vulnerabilities
[ ] grep -r 'VITE_' src/ — no secret keys with VITE_ prefix
[ ] npm run build && grep -r 'sk_live|secret' dist/ — returns empty
[ ] RLS patient isolation test — patient query returns only own rows
[ ] Admin lockout test — patient role cannot reach /dashboard/admin
[ ] XSS probe — <script>alert(1)</script> in name field is stripped
[ ] Supabase security advisor — zero WARN or ERROR advisories
[ ] HTTPS enforced — no HTTP fallback in production
```
